="image-wth-two-cta-and-links">                 <div class="image-two-cta-links-component">         <div class="image-two-cta-container">             <div class="image-container"><img class="image-two-cta-links-img" src="/img/TS-48091_CTV_Mapping_Project_-_Poker_Games_CTV_Blast_Teaser-1628837534056_tcm1488-527978.jpg" alt="blast-game" loading="lazy"></div>             <div class="two-cta-container">                                                                  <div class="cta-template cta-blue-white-border">         <a href="/download-poker/" onclick="_commonjs888.push({'function':'SmartAction.OpenAndDownload','values':['17030','888poker','/download-poker/']});">                 <span class="label">DOWNLOAD</span>                          </a>     </div>                                                                                    <div class="cta-template cta-blue-white-border">         <a href="javascript:void(0);" onclick="_commonjs888.push({'function':'SmartAction.SmartNoDownload','values':['17029','tab']});">                 <span class="label">Instant Play</span>                          </a>     </div>                               </div>         </div>         <div class="image-two-link-container">                                                      <div class="cta-template cta-blue-underline">         <a href="/poker-games/blast-game/">                 <span class="label">HOW TO PLAY</span>                          </a>     </div>                                                 </div>     </div>    </div>   </div>                  </div>             </div>                              </div></div> <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component pt-medium">     <div class="text"><h2>Try 888poker’s interactive poker tutorial</h2><br><p>Our interactive poker tutorial brings together all you need to know to start playing the following poker games, including Hold’em, Omaha Hi, Omaha Hi-Lo, BLAST and SNAP.</p></div> </div></div> <div class="iframe-component">                <div class="iframe-container">         <div class="iframe-wrapper">             <iframe src="https://www.888poker.com/poker/the-game/" width="100%" height="400" frameborder="0"></iframe>         </div>     </div> </div> <div class="title">        <div class="title-component pt-xlarge pb-medium">     <h2 class="h2 text-left">         Get to know the Best Poker Games at 888poker     </h2> </div> </div> <div class="grid"><div class="grid-component">                                                      <div class="column-container  two-columns-50">                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component">     <div class="text"><p style="padding-bottom: 0.0px; margin-bottom: 0.0px;"><img src="/img/TS-33563_TexasHoldem-text-area_Logo-1550839981487_tcm1488-434862.png"></p> <div class="lobby-strip-text box-item2"><h3>Texas Hold'em</h3> <p>Texas Hold’em is considered the purest of all poker games by many poker players and is still the most popular format played online. If you’re a new player, there’s no better game to play than Texas Hold’em to get you up to speed with the basic rules and strategy – plus it’s a lot of fun learning how to master the poker genre!</p> <p>Find out how to up your poker play on our <a href="/poker-games/texas-holdem" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Texas Hold'em page</a></p> </div></div> </div></div>                 <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component">     <div class="text"><p style="padding-bottom: 0.0px; margin-bottom: 0.0px;"><img src="/img/TS-33563TS-33563_Omaha-HI-text-area_Logo-1550840029950_tcm1488-434866.png"></p> <div class="lobby-strip-text box-item2"><h3>Omaha Hi</h3> <p>If Texas Hold’em poker is the most popular poker game online, then Omaha is a close second. In Omaha, you get dealt 4 starting cards to make a hand – although you can and must only use 2 hole cards and the best five cards win. This feature makes for an exciting and action-packed game where the flops can promise staggering amounts of draws.</p> <p>Discover how Omaha can improve your poker game on our <a href="/poker-games/omaha/" target="_blank">Omaha Hi games page!</a></p> </div></div> </div></div>   </div>                  </div>                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component">     <div class="text"><p style="padding-bottom: 0.0px; margin-bottom: 0.0px;"><img src="/img/TS-33563TS-33563_Omaha-HI-LO-text-area_Logo-1550840019498_tcm1488-434865.png"></p> <div class="lobby-strip-text box-item2"><h3>Omaha Hi-Lo</h3> <p>Omaha Hi-Lo is a draw heavy version of Omaha Hi where you can win pots with 2 made hands – a high hand and a low hand. Each winner will receive 50% of the pot at showdown. With two chances to win, players can go for a scoop where they win both the high and the low ends of the pot, holding the best 5-card hands.</p> <p>Start your poker journey with us on the <a href="/poker-games/omaha-hi-lo/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Omaha Hi-Lo Games page</a>.</p> </div></div> </div></div>   </div>                  </div>             </div>                              </div></div> <div class="grid"><div class="grid-component">                                                      <div class="column-container  two-columns-50">                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component">     <div class="text"><p style="padding-bottom: 0.0px; margin-bottom: 0.0px;"><img src="/img/TS-33563TS-33563_Snap-text-area_Logo-1550840042113_tcm1488-434867.png"></p> <div class="lobby-strip-text box-item2"><h3>Snap</h3> <p>Snap Poker is one of the fastest ways to play poker online. As soon as you quick-fold a hand, you are instantly seated at another table and dealt a new one.<br> <br> Say goodbye to waiting for your opponents to act and say hello to fast-paced poker action – just the way you like to play.</p> </div></div> </div></div>                 <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component">     <div class="text"><p style="padding-bottom: 0.0px; margin-bottom: 0.0px;"><img src="/img/TS-33563TS-33563_Blast-text-area_Logo-1550840008594_tcm1488-434864.png"></p> <div class="lobby-strip-text box-item2"><h3>BLAST</h3> <p>BLAST Sit &amp; Go’s are 4-handed poker games, where you get to play for prize pools up to 10,000 x your buy-in! Once seated, the action starts off as usual in a regular Texas Hold’em tournament. But once the BLAST timer strikes, all players are put all-in into just one lucky player stands victorious.</p> <p>Want to have a go? Check out our <a href="/poker-games/blast-game/" target="_blank">BLAST games here</a></p> </div></div> </div></div>   </div>                  </div>                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component">     <div class="text"><p style="padding-bottom: 0.0px; margin-bottom: 0.0px;"><img src="/img/TS-33563_PKO-text-area_Logo-1550839950962_tcm1488-434861.png"></p> <div class="lobby-strip-text box-item2"><h3>Progressive Knockouts (PKO)</h3> <p>Progressive Knockout tournaments (PKO’s) are the next best thing in poker. With bounties on the line, players can recoup their buy-ins without having to wait to make it into the money. As players progress, their bounties start to increase, and if you outlast everyone else, you get to collect your own bounty!</p> <p>Want to have a go? Check out our PKO games <a href="/poker-games/pko/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">here</a></p> </div></div> </div></div>   </div>                  </div>             </div>                              </div></div> <div class="container responsivegrid">  <div class="pt-medium pb-medium">     <div class="container-wrapper main-container">                             <div id="container-5e50837953" class="cmp-container">                  <div class="rich-text">            </div>               </div>      </div> </div></div> <div class="grid"><div class="grid-component">                                                      <div class="column-container  two-columns-50">                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="title">        <div class="title-component">     <h3 class="h3 text-left">         Poker Cash Games     </h3> </div> </div>                 <div class="text-with-icon">             <div class="text-with-icon-component">          <div class="text-with-icon-template layout-left">         <div class="image-container">                                              <picture>                  <img src="/img/01_1446739928331_tcm1488-263512.png" width="80" height="80" alt="24/7" loading="lazy">     </picture>          </div>         <div class="text-container">                              <div class="text"><noscript> <img src="/img/01_1446739928331_tcm1488-263512.png"></noscript> <p class="rich-text">The <a href="/real-money-poker/">Cash PokerGames</a> at 888poker run all day and all night long. So, there's no need to sit around, fidgeting in your seat, waiting for a table to fill up to start playing. You can get in there and start pushing players around, right away!</p></div>         </div>     </div>  </div></div>                 <div class="text-with-icon">             <div class="text-with-icon-component">          <div class="text-with-icon-template layout-left">         <div class="image-container">                                              <picture>                  <img src="/img/02_1446739942248_tcm1488-263513.png" width="80" height="80" alt="man thinking" loading="lazy">     </picture>          </div>         <div class="text-container">                              <div class="text"><noscript> <img src="/img/02_1446739942248_tcm1488-263513.png" alt="man thinking"></noscript> <p class="rich-text">888poker offers cash tables in a lot of different poker formats. You can find cash tables with Blast, SNAP, Texas Hold’em, Omaha Hi, and Omaha Hi-Lo. So, if Hold'em isn't your favourite, you can easily get into another poker game that suits your tastes</p></div>         </div>     </div>  </div></div>                 <div class="text-with-icon">             <div class="text-with-icon-component">          <div class="text-with-icon-template layout-left">         <div class="image-container">                                              <picture>                  <img src="/img/03_1446739950056_tcm1488-263514.png" width="80" height="80" alt="cent" loading="lazy">     </picture>          </div>         <div class="text-container">                              <div class="text"><noscript> <img src="/img/03_1446739950056_tcm1488-263514.png" alt="cent"></noscript> <p class="rich-text">If you're the kind of person who likes to come and go as they please, Cash Games are the perfect fit. You have full control and can sit in and post your blinds right away. Play for 10 minutes or 10 hours, it's up to you</p></div>         </div>     </div>  </div></div>   </div>                  </div>                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="title">        <div class="title-component">     <h3 class="h3 text-left">         Poker Tournament Games     </h3> </div> </div>                 <div class="text-with-icon">             <div class="text-with-icon-component">          <div class="text-with-icon-template layout-left">         <div class="image-container">                                              <picture>                  <img src="/img/04_1446739962152_tcm1488-263515.png" width="80" height="80" alt="chips" loading="lazy">     </picture>          </div>         <div class="text-container">                              <div class="text"><noscript> <img src="/img/04_1446739962152_tcm1488-263515.png" alt="chips"></noscript> <p class="rich-text">Most professional players love <a href="/poker-tournaments">pokertournaments</a>. Why? Because you can buy in for small amounts (or even for nothing) and win huge piles of cash and amazing prizes. And if you win big, you could even retire early!</p></div>         </div>     </div>  </div></div>                 <div class="text-with-icon">             <div class="text-with-icon-component">          <div class="text-with-icon-template layout-left">         <div class="image-container">                                              <picture>                  <img src="/img/05_1446739985560_tcm1488-263517.png" width="80" height="80" alt="tournament tickets" loading="lazy">     </picture>          </div>         <div class="text-container">                              <div class="text"><noscript> <img src="/img/05_1446739985560_tcm1488-263517.png" alt="tournament tickets"></noscript> <p class="rich-text">Once you've paid your buy-in to a tourney, you get to play for as long as the chips last. No need to re-buy or top up. You get to see a lot more hands for your Loonies and can learn a lot from just sitting and watching other players go nuts!</p></div>         </div>     </div>  </div></div>                 <div class="text-with-icon">             <div class="text-with-icon-component">          <div class="text-with-icon-template layout-left">         <div class="image-container">                                              <picture>                  <img src="/img/06_1446739995826_tcm1488-263516.png" width="80" height="80" alt="poker table" loading="lazy">     </picture>          </div>         <div class="text-container">                              <div class="text"><noscript> <img src="/img/06_1446739995826_tcm1488-263516.png" alt="poker table"></noscript> <p class="rich-text">In general, Tournaments are relatively low risk. You pay one amount and that's it. For your buy-in, you could get as much as 10K – 20K chips. Although the more common starting stack is around $2K – 3K.</p></div>         </div>     </div>  </div></div>   </div>                  </div>             </div>                              </div></div> <div class="title">        <div class="title-component">     <h2 class="h2 text-left">         Learn How to Play Other Poker Variations     </h2> </div> </div> <div class="grid"><div class="grid-component">                                                      <div class="column-container  two-columns-50">                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="image">           <div class="image-component img-100% None None">       <div class="image-container js-modal-open modal-enabled">                               <picture>                  <img src="/img/poker_games_bottom_image_tcm1987-497293-1625035767032_tcm1488-434871.jpg" width="600" height="338" alt="poker_games_bottom_image_tcm1987-497293-1625035767032_tcm1488-434871" loading="lazy">     </picture>       </div>                        <div class="modal js-modal js-modal-close">                <div class="modal-dialog">                     <div class="modal-content js-modal-content">                          <button class="button-close js-modal-button" title="Close (Esc)" aria-label="Close (Esc)">×</button>                                              <picture>                  <img class="modal-image js-modal-image" src="/img/poker_games_bottom_image_tcm1987-497293-1625035767032_tcm1488-434871.jpg" width="600" height="338" alt="poker_games_bottom_image_tcm1987-497293-1625035767032_tcm1488-434871" loading="lazy">     </picture>                      </div>                </div>           </div>       </div> </div>   </div>                  </div>                 <div class="column">                     <div class="parsys">                   <div class="rich-text">            <div class="rich-text-component None None">     <div class="text"> <p>Poker isn’t all Texas Hold’em and Omaha. There are many other <a href="/magazine/strategy/poker-variations">variations</a> that youcan learn to play. </p> <p>At <strong>888poker</strong>, we have easy-to-follow articles and guides to help along the way! </p> <p>Check out our step-by-step <strong>poker guides</strong> for these less popular, but equallyenticing, poker games:</p> <br> <strong>5 Card Draw</strong> <p>Five Card <a href="/magazine/strategy/5-card-draw">(5 Card) Draw</a>is a draw variant of poker. Players will hold and discard cards, replacing them with cards inthe deck.<br> </p> <strong>HORSE</strong> <p><a href="/magazine/strategy/horse-poker">HORSE</a> is an acronymthat includes 5 different poker variants. They are: Hold’em, Omaha Hi/Lo, Razz (Stud Lo), Stud(Stud Hi), and Eight-or-Better (Stud Hi/Lo).<br></p> <strong>Razz</strong> <p><a href="/magazine/strategy/razz-poker">Razz</a> is a form of StudPoker. In the ranking system for this game, straights and flushes do not count against a lowhand.<br></p> <strong>2-7 Triple Draw</strong> <p>In 2-7 <a href="/magazine/strategy/2-7-triple-draw">Triple Draw</a>,players receive their own individual 5-card hand. And they have not one, but three draw attemptsto make the best “low” hand. <br> </p> <strong>5-Card Omaha</strong> <p>In<a href="/magazine/strategy/5-card-omaha"> 5-Card Omaha</a>,instead of being dealt four hole cards, each player receives five. They can only use two of thefour to make the best hand. <br> </p> <strong>Badugi</strong> <p>This poker variant falls under the “draw” and “Lowball” poker families. But <a href="/magazine/strategy/badugi-poker">Badugi</a> uses a uniquehand ranking system to determine the best hand. <br> </p> <strong>Chinese Poker</strong> <p>In <a href="/magazine/poker-world/intro-to-chinese-poker">Chinese poker</a>, players each receive13 initial cards. They must divide these cards into threedifferent poker hands, attempting to make the best/highest-ranked holdings. <br> </p> <strong>Short Deck</strong> <p>In <a href="/magazine/strategy/why-you-should-be-playing-short-deck-poker">Short Deck </a> poker, all deuces, threes, fours, and fives are removed from the deck – leaving 36cards. This difference can result in a more action-packed game. <br> </p></div> </div></div>   </div>                  </div>             </div>                              </div></div>               </div>      </div> </div></div>               </div>      </div> </div></div><?php include_once ($_SERVER["DOCUMENT_ROOT"]."/footer.php"); ?>